# Model config: gpt-oss-20b (native MXFP4 MoE, sliding-window attention)
#
# Sourced by the generic launchers when MODEL_CONF=gpt-oss-20b (or `run.sh gpt-oss-20b`).
# Sets the model path plus per-model tuning. Everything here is a default (:=) so inline
# env and trailing CLI args still override.
#
# Rationale:
#   - KV cache f16, NOT q8_0: MoE weights are already MXFP4 and several layers use
#     sliding-window attention; quantizing KV on top measurably hurts quality, and the
#     cache is small enough that f16 fits easily.
#   - Wider batches prefill faster on gpt-oss.
#   - OpenAI's recommended sampling is temp 1.0 / top-p 1.0 (do not lower).
#   - --reasoning-format auto exposes the reasoning channel via the chat template;
#     set effort with e.g. --chat-template-kwargs '{"reasoning_effort":"high"}'.

: "${MODEL:=gpt-oss-20b/gpt-oss-20b-mxfp4.gguf}"
: "${CACHE_TYPE_K:=f16}"
: "${CACHE_TYPE_V:=f16}"
: "${UBATCH:=4096}"
: "${BATCH:=4096}"

LLAMA_ARGS+=(--temp 1.0 --top-p 1.0 --reasoning-format auto)
